# EcoSphere AI — Implementation Plan

## Overview

**EcoSphere AI** is a production-quality, hackathon-winning SaaS web application that helps users understand, measure, track, and reduce their carbon footprint using AI-driven insights, behavioral analytics, gamification, and actionable recommendations.

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Framework | React 19 + TypeScript + Vite |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui |
| Animation | Framer Motion |
| Routing | React Router v7 |
| Forms | React Hook Form + Zod |
| Charts | Recharts |
| Icons | Lucide React |
| State | React Context + localStorage persistence |
| AI | Simulated AI engine with realistic responses (no API key required — fully self-contained) |
| Maps | Leaflet + OpenStreetMap (no API key required) |
| Auth | Local auth simulation with full UX flow |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Design Philosophy**: Since this is a hackathon demo, all features will be **fully functional and self-contained** — no external API keys, no Supabase credentials needed. The app uses localStorage for persistence, a built-in AI engine with pre-trained response patterns, and OpenStreetMap for maps. This means **anyone can clone and run it instantly**.

## Architecture

```
React App (SPA)
├── Auth Layer (Context + localStorage)
├── Data Layer (localStorage + seed data)
├── AI Engine (rule-based + template responses)
├── Carbon Calculator (real emission factors)
├── Gamification Engine (XP, levels, badges, streaks)
├── Visualization Layer (Recharts + Framer Motion)
└── Theme System (Dark/Light + CSS variables)
```

